The IRS has made strides in improving computer security, but vulnerabilities persist, risking taxpayer data theft.
Efforts to catch unauthorized file access are limited, prompting the need for personal shredders to safeguard sensitive information.
Vice President Al Gore emphasizes the importance of protecting privacy in the digital age, proposing initiatives to enhance data security.
Identity theft cases, like Santner's elaborate scheme, highlight the urgency for stricter regulations.
Employers increasingly rely on background checks, raising concerns about accuracy and privacy.
Check fraud remains a significant issue, costing banks billions annually.
